Venezuela bolivar closes stable in slow market . The Venezuelan bolivar closed virtually unchanged at 476 . 25 / 476 . 75 per dollar on Tuesday , compared with 476 . 25 / 476 . 60 per dollar on Monday , in slow , stable trading , dealers said . " The market was fairly quiet . The spread remains tight and the Central Bank has not had to intervene , " one said . Dealers said the market was extremely slow in the afternoon and saw no reason for a sharp swing in the exchange rate Wednesday . - - Silene Ramirez , Caracas newsroom , 582 834405 
